{"id": 231226684, "title": "Awright ya bawbag: Hollywood star Jared Leto learns Glaswegian phrases after kilted appearance at The Hydro", "text": "Alongside his illustrious film career, including roles in The Thin Red Line, American Psycho, Fight Club and winning an Oscar for Dallas Buyers Club, has been the frontman of rock band Thirty Seconds to Mars for over 20 years. He has a history of wearing a kilt onstage as part of his stage persona and for their gig at The Hydro both Jared and elder brother Shannon - the group\u2019s drummer - work punk kilts designed by Siobhan Mackenzie. Her Glasgow based company produces contemporary fashion for menswear and womenswear, inspired by Scotland with a strong tartan motif. She shared a picture of the pair, explaining: \u201cJared wears a full custom look including a tartan faced sequin cape, mesh crystal top and crystal lovers kilt. Shannon wears a multi-tartan punk kilt.\u201d After the show, Leto shared a clip of him learning Glaswegian phrases with his 12 million followers on Instagram. You can watch the Hollywood star attempt to say \u201caway and bile yer heid\u201d and other colourful parts of the Glasgow patter lexicon here.", "summary": "<p>Actor and Thirty Seconds to Mars frontman Jared Leto  </p>", "url": "https://www.glasgowworld.com/whats-on/music/awright-ya-bawbag-hollywood-star-jared-leto-learns-glaswegian-phrases-after-kilted-appearance-at-the-hydro-4658312", "image": "https://www.glasgowworld.com/jpim-static/image/2024/06/08/10/31/Screenshot%202024-06-08%20110401.jpg?width=1200&enable=upscale", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 12:35:58", "author": "Paul Trainer", "authors": ["Paul Trainer"], "language": "en", "catgory": "entertainment", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.563}